##Self-rescue in the shock of three industries in Wuhan

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Under the impact of the epidemic, the position of Wuhan Automobile Industry in the global supply chain is more critical than the less integrated medical manufacturing industry and the photoelectronic industry based on partial import substitution

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wen | Caijing reporter, Kang yun-chang, Li sin-in, intern reporter, Su Peng

Editor | Wang Yanchun, Chi Leung

Located in the center city of Wuhan's Light Valley Millet Base, a number of factories quiet no one, the past shuttle trucks also disappeared.

"The epidemic has affected a wide range of electronic products, including mobile phones, headsets, mobile power supplies and air purifiers, as well as chip procurement, Mold Opening, assembly, batching and transportation, " Lou Xiaoyin, Xiaomi's overseas sales director, told CAIJING. One or two links in the upstream and downstream supply chain are shut down and the impact on the whole supply chain is significant."

Three years ago, Lei Jun, a graduate of Wuhan University, led Xiaomi, Jinshan, and Shunwei into Wuhan's Guanggu, planning to build a whole ecosystem of Xiaomi in Wuhan in the next few years. With the closure of Wuhan, a number of production lines are facing "closure. ". "We are assessing the extent of supply chain volatility overseas and taking contingency or temporary measures to try to maintain the stability of the supply chain while waiting for overseas markets to recover in the second half of the year. "

Among Wuhan's pillar industries, auto manufacturing was the hardest hit by the outbreak. Dongfeng Motor Group is the leading automobile company in Wuhan and Hubei Province, employing about 140,000 employees. Wuhan "closed city" So far, Dongfeng Motor has stopped production for more than a month, "the date of resumption of production unknown.

Like Xiaomi, Dongfeng Motor, most of the manufacturing enterprises in Wuhan face the broken chain of the industrial chain. Wuhan has a large-scale industrial cluster in automobile and parts, optoelectronic information, biomedicine and Medical Devices, and is a key node in domestic and even global supply chain.

This epidemic is like a stone falling into the lake, the wave center of Wuhan Industry Vibration, resulting in shock waves gradually to the outer layers of ripples.

"although the automobile industry in Wuhan has almost shut down, the telecommunications and electronics industry has not shut down and the impact on it in the short term can be controlled, " an official from the Wuhan municipal government in Hubei Province told CAIJING, china's automobile market consumption is weak, the automobile industry has been affected, but communication electronics, bio-pharmaceutical as a representative of the strategic emerging industry suddenly emerged as the most beautiful economic scenery in Wuhan.

The reporter's investigation found that due to the extension of the holiday and the traffic control in the provinces, the return of personnel from the two major industries of telecommunications, electronics and biomedicine was less than expected at present, but with the efforts of the enterprises, the epidemic has less impact on the two major industries, most of them work nonstop.

Tang Dajie, director of the Research Department of the Sai Yi Enterprise Research Institute, said that most of the upstream high-tech enterprises, such as telecommunications electronics and biomedicine, are technology-intensive, and can still solve the problem of resuming work by working remotely, but the middle and lower reaches of the industrial chain are mostly labor-intensive manufacturing enterprises, such as the chip factory, mobile phone Oem, there is a shortage of workers, enterprise capacity weakened, capital chain tension.

China's domestic recruitment platform BOSS Zhipin and city service recruitment platform store manager zhipin jointly released the "blue-collar resume work progress observation" , announcing that the average return of blue-collar workers in three industries in 15 new first-tier cities in China is 47% , wuhan blue-collar workers to resume work progress of 33% .

The shock of Wuhan Automobile Industry

Wuhan Economic and Technological Development Zones has a 13 km "Dongfeng Road" , it runs through the north-south, the world's automobile industry is one of the most concentrated axis. There are also 12 automobile assembly plants and more than 500 spare parts enterprises, with an annual output of more than one million vehicles.

Wuhan is a well-deserved center of the car capital, the automobile industry has been the first pillar industry in Wuhan for nine years. In 2018, the city produced 1.7 million vehicles, accounting for 6 percent of the country's total, and its auto and parts industries, including Dongfeng Honda, Dongfeng, dongfeng-PSA, dongfeng-Reno and SAIC GM, have a total output value of 400 billion yuan, including France, Japan, the United States, independent of the four major car department.

This time, not only Wuhan, Han River as a chain, including Wuhan, Xiangyang, Shiyan and other places linked to the thousands of miles of the automotive industry zone are in crisis.

As the headquarters of Dongfeng Motor, Hubei Gathers more than half of its production capacity. To this end, Dongfeng Motor told the "financial" reporter, the company's management continued to meet to study the upstream and downstream dealers, suppliers in order to do a good job in risk management, market dynamics. Company employees began to use the telephone, mail, video and other means of remote network office.

The impact of the factory shutdown is far-reaching. As BCG's Boston consulting group points out in its research paper, continued shutdowns at local plants will also lead to a shortage of needed vehicles at dealerships and a failure of radical suppliers.

Lang Xuehong, deputy secretary-general of the China Automobile Circulation Association, told Caijing that although the dealers can digest their existing stocks at this stage, taking into account the pace at which the manufacturers will resume production, some models, such as Nissan and Honda, will be in short supply.

The industry had expected that year after the SARS epidemic, car sales demand blowout again. However, Edmund Wilson, an auto consultancy, said in a research note that sales nationwide would fall by more than 50% in the first quarter of this year compared with the same period last year.

Lang Xuehong is concerned that although at this stage dealers have started 80% , but the overall consumer demand is weak, which will be counter-productive to the existing capacity.

By the current domestic car purchase demand is sluggish, for large-scale production, some car companies sense of urgency is not strong. An international parts giant executive told CAIJING that the parts company's non-hubei factories were already operating, and it was clear that the demand for vehicles from different factories was very different.

Hubei Province has a large network of auto parts suppliers, with more than 700 in total serving domestic vehicle manufacturers, including local brands and joint venture brands, and a small number of export customers abroad.

Pricewaterhousecoopers China reports that about 40 percent of the world's top 10 suppliers'production plants and R & D centers are in the hard-hit areas.

The scale effect of industrial agglomeration has effectively reduced the cost of R & D, production, logistics and so on. However, when companies start to rely too heavily on one supplier and emphasize lean management of low inventories, they make the supply chain extremely vulnerable.

The selection of alternative parts suppliers is not easy, even in some areas there is no alternative, once the critical parts supply means that the whole production will stop.

A Wuhan Vehicle Factory staff told the "CAIJING" reporter, the company in accordance with the plan to resume work on March 10 to prepare, but all that remains uncertain.

Li Ping (not his real name) , a middle-level manager at Geely Automobile's Wuhan Branch, has worked for five years as a chinese-owned brand. "In the short term, Wuhan auto companies don't have the conditions to resume work because they can't guarantee the safety of their employees, " he said

It is understood that most of the employees of Wuhan Automobile and parts enterprises are Hubei people, and many of the front-line employees live in counties and cities around Wuhan, and are still isolated in some counties and cities around Wuhan. Li Ping is currently isolated in a small town in Jianghan District, Wuhan. For the people of Hubei who are separated from each other at home, it is uncertain when they will be able to return to work and when the closure of the city will end.

Xu Haidong, Assistant secretary-general of the China Association of Automobile Industry, told Caijing that comprehensive analysis shows that the impact of the suspension of production and further spread of the local automobile industry in Hubei and Wuhan due to the new pneumonia may last until the end of March.

Earlier, Beijing mercedes-benz's "letter of help" went viral on the Internet. "The company has only one day of safe stock, and any suspension of production for more than one day will result in the suspension of Beijing Benz Production. If Beijing Benz does not return to work on February 10, the economic losses will exceed RMB400M A day, can approve its 19 parts enterprises to resume normal work on February 10. For now, beijing-based mercedes-benz says it has resumed production at its factory on a single shift.

Trouble is, some countries and enterprises to prevent the spread of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, refused to order goods, canceled the original order. According to the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers, more than 60 countries have issued entry control measures against China, which has hindered Chinese auto companies from expanding into overseas markets and made it more difficult for them to export cars and parts.

To this end, some parts companies are still trying to ensure that priority overseas supply, in order to maintain the build-up of good reputation.

Overseas companies will also face a high price for "allergies" . In the steering wheel, steering column and steering box categories, more than 20 percent of China's exports of steering systems to the United States come from Wuhan. Any disruption in supply from these plants could have a huge ripple effect on assembly plants in North America. If you need to remold, train workers, the entire construction period of three to nine months.

In response, an executive of a component company said that the outbreak was a force majeure factor and that the auto industry was a fully competitive Red Sea market. The dilemma was to resist risks and reduce costs. The only way to solve the problem was to look at the solid foundation of each entrepreneur, to set up a risk response plan.

Electronic Information, bio-pharmaceutical enterprises to save themselves

CAIJING reporters understand that as early as the 12th five-year plan period, the Wuhan government proposed to build six "hundred billion industrial clusters" , such as electronic information, automobiles, equipment manufacturing and steel.

According to information released by the Wuhan Development and Reform Bureau, after years of efforts, giants such as tencent, Huawei, Xiaomi and Xiaohongshu have gradually established branches such as branch offices and research and development centers in Wuhan by the end of 2018, there are more than 60 Internet companies with headquarters and second headquarters in Wuhan. Wuhan has established three industrial chains: Communication Optoelectronics, energy optoelectronics and consumer optoelectronics. At present, Wuhan is the largest manufacturer of optical fiber and cable in the world, accounting for two-thirds of China's domestic market and one-quarter of the international market.

The sudden outbreak of the Wuhan Automobile Industry Not only disrupted the production rhythm, but also to a large extent, the electronics and optical communications equipment manufacturing industry in Wuhan formed no small impact.

The Yangtze River storage national storage base, built by the Central Government in Wuhan in 2016, is one of the iconic enterprises in China's development of the integrated circuit industry, the Wuhan city government official told Caijing, the outbreak has reduced the production capacity of the national storage base on the Yangtze River to about half of its daily capacity.

Since the outbreak of the epidemic, the operation of the national storage base of the Yangtze River has attracted the attention of the people in the communication and electronics industries. According to the source from the base, the company is currently actively coordinating with government departments, and under the premise of ensuring safety, production and operation are proceeding normally and in an orderly manner, effectively avoiding the possible impact of power cuts and production suspensions. At the same time, the company has adopted separate management and control measures by district, in order to avoid the introduction of external virus, the staff stationed at the plant has not been infected with the case.

"Chip" (semiconductor component products collectively) is the basic component of the communication and electronics industry. CAIJING reporter learned that during the outbreak, the three chip enterprises in Wuhan . Yang Daohong, chairman of Wuhan Xinxin, said that the company had sufficient raw materials for production and implemented grading and closed management for its employees. Apart from a slight delay in research and development, the company basically maintained its schedule. Currently, the company has applied to the relevant parties to expand bandwidth support, so that more than 5,000 employees can guarantee the company's remote online office.

People at Semiconductor Industry, a leading research firm in China, predict that many of the upstream and midstream companies in the Semiconductor industry chain will continue to operate sustainably, the downstream chip sealing and testing enterprises face the biggest challenge, and the main challenges are the operational difficulties such as insufficient personnel on duty, poor material transportation, and unfavorable capital turnover, and in the second half of the year to digest a large backlog of demand capacity constraints.

Overall, the impact of the epidemic on China's integrated circuit industry is relatively limited.

A number of industry insiders suggest that the outbreak of the recent two years, the impact of new chip companies are more obvious. A newly created manufacturing enterprise, especially one where the equipment is already partially in place, can not install and debug the equipment, the factory can only be at a standstill, the depreciation of fixed assets and the salaries of employees are under great pressure, and the risk of cash flow disruption is relatively high, to be hit by an outbreak would be to make it worse. It is suggested that the Wuhan municipal government should pay special attention to these new chip enterprises and give them special support.

According to professional analysts, the first quarter is also the traditionally low season for the Semiconductor industry. The Semiconductor industry is expected to see a retaliatory rebound in the second quarter, particularly in the second half of the year, as the outbreak gradually eases and improves. Once the epidemic is over, previously suppressed industrial demand will be fully released, and the Semiconductor industry's long term positive trend will not change.

Biomedical and medical device companies are also an important pillar industry in Wuhan. It is learned that there are more than 1,500 biomedical and medical device companies in Wuhan, including Fortune 500 companies such as Pfizer of the United States, Bayer of Germany and Fresenius Kirby of Germany, there are also China's Renfu Pharmaceutical Group, Sinopharm Holdings and other large pharmaceutical enterprises. According to the Ministry of Science and Technology, in 2018, Wuhan's national bio-industry base ranked third in China in terms of overall strength.

The Wuhan government said that from the 2019 three pillar industries in the city's total industrial output value of the proportion of view, biomedical and Medical Equipment Enterprises Faster Development.

Many biomedical enterprises in Wuhan did not stop production this Spring Festival, running continuously, or donated drugs, or to assist in the distribution of medical supplies, to fight the epidemic in the first line.

According to the reporter of Caijing, at present, most of the biomedical and medical device enterprises in Wuhan operate from home. Chen Huang, deputy general manager of Wuhan Haite Biopharmaceutical Co. , a listed a-share company, said that at present, everything including investor relations management, intermediary communication, and regulatory coordination are conducted online, for example, with the help of video conferencing and telephone communication tools, some of the company's projects for demonstration.

Wuhan, an important manufacturing base in China, has been hit hard by the outbreak and will take some time to recover. But Song Xuetao, a macro analyst at Tianfeng Securities, believes that in the future, as the epidemic gradually weakens, Wuhan's consumer and service sectors will gradually repair, and the pulse of pharmaceutical biology will gradually subside. In the long run, the impact of the epidemic on the manufacturing industry chain will gradually disappear as the epidemic weakens and industrial production resumes.

For Enterprises, after the epidemic, how to improve the supply chain planning and management resilience, restructuring the supply chain crisis response system, is the most practical problem.
